cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

This paper is about using model-predictive control and task representations to efficiently learn new robotic skills directly on a real robot, and transfer them from simulation to the real world. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper proposes a novel approach to learning skills and policies. The paper also involves computer vision (cs.CV) and control systems (cs.SY), as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques.
